# VNets and Subnets

## What This Is
It's about how virtual networks work in azure, subnetting them and how to do it in the portal.

## What I Built
I made a virtual network in azure called samNet for sample net. It's ipv4 with a network set to 10.0.0.0/16. I made three subnets within this network. The first is snet-frontend with a starting address of 10.0.1.0/24. The second is snet-backend with a starting address of 10.0.2.0/24 and the last is snet-db with a starting address of 10.0.3.0/24.

## Why I Made These Choices
I made these choices as part of my lab activity within a study guide i have. But also it showed me a bit how to logically separate my networks.

